{"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Fitting a Robust Regression Model using RANSAC\n","\n","Linear regression models can be heavily impacted by outliers. Instead of manually identifying and throwing out outliers (which requires subjective judgment and domain knowledge), we can use a robust method called **RANdom SAmple Consensus (RANSAC)**.\n","\n","RANSAC works by fitting a regression model to a subset of the data known as **inliers**.\n","\n","## The RANSAC Algorithm\n","\n","The iterative RANSAC algorithm can be summarized in the following steps:\n","\n","1. Select a random number of examples to be inliers and fit the model.\n","2. Test all other data points against the fitted model and add those points that fall within a user-given tolerance to the inliers.\n","3. Refit the model using all inliers.\n","4. Estimate the error of the fitted model versus the inliers.\n","5. Terminate the algorithm if the performance meets a certain user-defined threshold or if a fixed number of iterations was reached; go back to *step 1* otherwise.\n","\n","---"],"metadata":{"id":"f2glslYh_9Mb"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 1. Implementing RANSAC with Scikit-Learn\n","\n","We can implement this using scikit-learn's `RANSACRegressor` class in combination with a linear model."],"metadata":{"id":"6Xu48SueBCns"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["import pandas as pd\n","\n","# Define the subset of columns to use\n","columns = ['Gr Liv Area', 'SalePrice']\n","\n","# Load the dataset\n","df = pd.read_csv('http://jse.amstat.org/v19n3/decock/AmesHousing.txt',\n","                 sep='\\t',\n","                 usecols=columns)\n","\n","X = df[['Gr Liv Area']].values\n","y = df['SalePrice'].values"],"metadata":{"id":"OeeiVpxEBqgV","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1781858238087,"user_tz":-330,"elapsed":663,"user":{"displayName":"Gobisan Ananthanadarajan","userId":"08370486503672403873"}}},"execution_count":4,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["from sklearn.linear_model import RANSACRegressor\n","from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression\n","import numpy as np\n","import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n","\n","# Initialize the RANSAC regressor\n","ransac = RANSACRegressor(\n","    LinearRegression(),\n","    max_trials=100,           # Maximum number of iterations\n","    min_samples=0.95,         # Minimum number of randomly chosen training examples (95% of dataset)\n","    residual_threshold=None,  # Default threshold uses Median Absolute Deviation (MAD)\n","    random_state=123\n",")\n","\n","ransac.fit(X, y)"],"outputs":[{"output_type":"execute_result","data":{"text/plain":["RANSACRegressor(estimator=LinearRegression(), min_samples=0.95,\n","                random_state=123)"],"text/html":["<style>#sk-container-id-1 {\n","  /* Definition of color scheme common for light and dark mode */\n","  --sklearn-color-text: #000;\n","  --sklearn-color-text-muted: #666;\n","  --sklearn-color-line: gray;\n","  /* Definition of color scheme for unfitted estimators */\n","  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0: #fff5e6;\n","  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1: #f6e4d2;\n","  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2: #ffe0b3;\n","  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-3: chocolate;\n","  /* Definition of color scheme for fitted estimators */\n","  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-0: #f0f8ff;\n","  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-1: #d4ebff;\n","  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-2: #b3dbfd;\n","  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-3: cornflowerblue;\n","\n","  /* Specific color for light theme */\n","  --sklearn-color-text-on-default-background: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, black)));\n","  --sklearn-color-background: var(--sg-background-color, var(--theme-background, var(--jp-layout-color0, white)));\n","  --sklearn-color-border-box: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, black)));\n","  --sklearn-color-icon: #696969;\n","\n","  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {\n","